# Path Alias Imports

Always use path aliases when importing local modules (e.g., `@somelib/*` → `src/somelib/*`).

If path aliases are not configured, set them up in `tsconfig` before adding new local imports.

Example:

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
import { SomelibService } from '@somelib/somelib.service';

// ❌ BAD
import { SomelibService } from '../../somelib/somelib.service';
```
